The Error Handling The API uses standard HTTP error codes to indicate errors, with 401 Unauthorized indicating an invalid token and 500 Internal Server Error indicating a server-side error. In the event of an error, the API will return a JSON response with a detailed error message, as shown in the example below: 
{
  "error": "Invalid token",
  "code": 401
}
 Our support team, led by John Doe, is available to assist with any issues or questions.
